content:
Customize Your Chat Branding with Salesforce Sites

To customize your Chat implementation with images, use a Salesforce Site to upload the images for your chat window and chat buttons.

Available in: Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience
Available in: Performance Editions and Developer Edition orgs that were created after June 14, 2012
Available in: Essentials, Unlimited, and Enterprise Editions with Service Cloud or Sales Cloud

USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To create and edit Salesforce Sites: Customize Application

The legacy chat product is scheduled for retirement on February 14, 2026. To avoid service interruptions, migrate to Messaging for In-App and Web before that date.

Create a Salesforce Site to host your images.
Upload your branding images as static resources.
NOTE The maximum size for a standard chat window image is 50 pixels.

SEE ALSO
Create and Edit Salesforce Sites
Define Static Resources
title: Customizing Service Cloud Chat with Salesforce Sites
